The article discusses a briefing by OMB Director Peter Orszag on the FY2010 budget appendix and terminations, reductions, and savings. Orszag emphasizes the need for health care reform to address the unsustainable fiscal path. He also discusses the importance of making the rest of the government work better and eliminating inefficient programs. The briefing highlights $17 billion in savings for fiscal year 2010 and the focus on measuring what works and what doesn't to allocate resources more effectively. Orszag mentions the involvement of Congress in seeking savings and efficiencies. He also mentions the upcoming release of the Analytical Perspectives volume and historical tables for the budget. During the Q&A, Orszag addresses questions about revenue raisers from cap and trade, changes in economic assumptions, new programs, defense budget cuts, earmarks, and the process of evaluating programs for termination.